  "prompt": "Will people still be able to have websites with no net neutrality?",
  "response": "Yes, people will still be able to have websites without net neutrality, but the conditions may change. Without net neutrality protections, Internet Service Providers (ISPs) could potentially:\n\n1. Charge website owners more for faster access\n2. Create \"fast lanes\" and \"slow lanes\" for different types of content\n3. Potentially block or throttle access to certain websites\n\nThis means smaller websites might face challenges competing with larger, wealthier sites that can pay for better access. However, websites themselves will still exist - the primary concern is how easily users can access them.",
